org.apache.geode.security.generator

Class CredentialGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.geode.security.generator.CredentialGenerator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DummyCredentialGenerator, LdapUserCredentialGenerator, PKCSCredentialGenerator, SSLCredentialGenerator

    public abstract class CredentialGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
    Encapsulates obtaining valid and invalid credentials. Implementations will be for different kinds of authentication schemes.
    Since:
    GemFire 5.5

      • initialize

        protected abstract java.util.Properties initialize()
                                            throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initialize the credential generator. This is provided separately from the init() method for convenience of implementations so that they do not need to store in systemProperties. The latter is convenient for the users who do not need to store these properties rather can obtain it later by invoking getSystemProperties()

        Required to be implemented by concrete classes that implement this abstract class.

        Returns:
        A set of extra properties that should be added to Gemfire system properties when not null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when there is a problem during initialization
